title: Ethiopian FolkFunk
description:
This is a weird pearl. My girlfriend gave me this record. It's recorded in ethiopia in the 70'ties, when, in a short period, musicians were allowed to esperiment. The repetoire is folkloric but the instrumentation is typical afroamerican funk instruments, i.e.: wah-wah guitar, fender rhodes, saxofones etc...
Unfortunately I have no info on the artists nor title of the record.
